README file by Ciro Di Giovanni

As far as I am concerned, I have never read a readme file in my life. Unless when I was 11 back in 1995 and I was learning to use Windows 95 and wanted to know what was ll that about.
Back then I found a file called readme and I read it. As you can see, we still had no Internet. 
Today we have so much information that now I know why a readme file is necessary. For us developers to leave something more behing us. Like a little treasure map for the chosen ones. 
Anyway, maybe I am too romantic. Who knows? BUt isn't that what this is all about? Love?

Have a nice day,

Ciro 
